-- Germany to Hire 260 People for Energy Change, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-07-13T05:43:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/germany-to-hire-260-people-for-energy-change-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany  plans to hire 260 people at
the Federal Network Agency, the Economy Ministry and the
Ministry for the Environment to cope with its transition from
nuclear power to renewable energy,  Handelsblatt  reported today,
citing unidentified government officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  